<task id="SPE-013" project="SDAP SPE Admin App">
  <metadata>
    <title>List/Get Containers Endpoints</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>2h</estimated-effort>
    <tags>bff-api, api, graph, phase-1</tags>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <dependencies>SPE-006, SPE-009</dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>Implement the List and Get container endpoints so the SPE Admin App can retrieve containers from SharePoint Embedded via the BFF API. These endpoints form the foundation for all container management operations in the admin UI.</prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET developer familiar with Minimal APIs and Microsoft Graph</role>
  <goal>Two working endpoints that list containers (with pagination) and retrieve a single container by ID, both delegating to SpeAdminGraphService for Graph API calls.</goal>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">Use Minimal API endpoint pattern — no controllers, no Azure Functions.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Use endpoint filters for authorization — no global auth middleware.</constraint>
  </constraints>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/endpoint-definition.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/auth/graph-sdk-v5.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <context>
    <background>The SPE Admin App needs to display containers belonging to a specific container type configuration. The Graph API endpoint storage/fileStorage/containers supports listing and getting individual containers. The configId query parameter determines which SpeContainerTypeConfig (and therefore which container type) to query against.</background>
  </context>
  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Create endpoint class">Create ContainerEndpoints.cs in src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Endpoints/SpeAdmin/ with static MapContainerEndpoints extension method.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Implement list endpoint">Add GET /api/spe/containers?configId={id} that accepts configId, calls SpeAdminGraphService to list containers from Graph API storage/fileStorage/containers, and returns paginated results.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Implement get endpoint">Add GET /api/spe/containers/{containerId}?configId={id} that retrieves a single container by ID via SpeAdminGraphService.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Handle pagination">Support $top and $skipToken query parameters for pagination, mapping to Graph API OData pagination.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Register endpoints">Register MapContainerEndpoints in the endpoint registration pipeline.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Test endpoints">Verify both endpoints return expected container data and handle error cases (not found, unauthorized, invalid configId).</step>
  </steps>
  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Endpoints/SpeAdmin/ContainerEndpoints.cs</output>
  </outputs>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">GET /api/spe/containers?configId={id} returns a paginated list of containers for the specified container type config.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">GET /api/spe/containers/{containerId}?configId={id} returns a single container's details.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Invalid or missing configId returns 400 Bad Request with ProblemDetails.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Non-existent containerId returns 404 Not Found.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
